  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and<strong> chopped carrot</strong> to the pan</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softening</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the veg is softening, top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into thin discs</p><p>Grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 25ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[30ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>dried basil</strong> and <strong>umami seasoning</strong> – this is your <strong>savoury stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> drained lentils</strong>,<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and<strong> savoury stock</strong> to the pan</p><p>Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>lentil ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat, once melted, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> into the <strong>roux</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 3-4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>(Tip: Add a little water if the sauce is looking a little thick!) – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>lentil ragù </strong>over the bottom of an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with the <strong>courgette discs</strong></p><p>Cover with the <strong>béchamel sauce</strong>, top with the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong> and cook in the oven for 15-20 min or until bubbling and golden – this is your <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>lentil & courgette bake</strong></p><p>While the bake is cooking, wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-lentil-and-courgette-bake/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Leave the <strong>cheesy lentil & courgette bake</strong> to stand for a few min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p><p>Serve the<strong> cheesy lentil & courgette bake </strong>with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side<strong> </strong>and drizzle with a little<strong> olive oil </strong>and your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
